article.headline: High Point 115, Virginia Military 104
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored 32 points with 13 rebounds to lead High Point over VMI, 115-104, Wednesday night in a game in which the Panthers never trailed. High Point (11-5, 2-0 Big South Conference) went up by 20 with 4:20 to play before VMI closed to within seven with 40 seconds left -- the closest they got at the end. VMI's Reggie Williams led all scorers with 40 points and grabbed 16 rebounds. Chavis Holmes scored 25 and Travis Holmes added 19 for the Keydets (6-11, 0-2). Jerald Minnis added 27 points and Landon Quick had 22 for High Point. The Panthers shot 66 percent in the first half and led 63-48 at the break.
